window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Genres:</b> LitRPG / GameLit, Post-Apocalyptic, Adventure Fantasy</p> <p>Discovering that the system responsible for raising my stats might actually be \"aware\" left me speechless. <i>Literally</i>, since I was temporarily hit with a \"Stroke Ailment\" to shut me up.</p> <p>However, that just raised more questions and concerns, especially now that it was the clear this mysterious force wielded significantly more power over my life than I ever imagined.</p> <p>And worse, things were only going to get more complicated.</p> <p>New party members, more dangerous fights, and foreboding evolutions all threatened to upset the one goal I’d had since the very beginning - survive.</p> <p><b><i>Warning:</i></b><i> This book contains content that may not be suitable for all audiences, including excessive profanity and some violence/gore.</i> </p> <p><b>Prologue</b></p> <p>Savannah took a deep breath and let it out slowly, turning her head again to focus on the brilliant icy blue leaves blowing gently in the breeze.</p> <p>“I hate this,” she commented, only to abruptly look up at me in alarm, as if she was afraid of being misunderstood. “I’m thankful that you saved me,” she clarified. “But I just hate this system thing, and the fact that it’s putting us in danger.”</p> <p>“I know,” I replied simply. “I don’t like it much either. But we have to get stronger. <i>You</i> have to get stronger. Otherwise we might not be so lucky next time.” My tone became somber as I lowered my voice to a whisper. “It was a really close one. Too close.”</p> <p>Savannah shivered at the <i>too recent</i> memory, pushing more into me, and thus, shoving my folded wings more against the frame, as she turned to look at the <i>Foxfire Trees</i> endlessly burning in the darkness in a heatless blaze. </p> <p><b>Rise of the Night Stalkers 2</b> is a full-length novel.</p>"; 
